OL,3,CWhy I travelled the country asking
OL,4,CMuslims what Ramadan means to them
OL,6,FI've been fortunate enough to spend
OL,7,Ftime with British Muslim communities
OL,8,Ffrom London to Bradford to Aberdeen,
OL,9,Fto see how they observe this holy
OL,10,Fmonth and why this period means so
OL,11,Fmuch to so many.
OL,13,FI was particularly touched by the
OL,14,Fefforts being made across the country
OL,15,Fto ensure people felt included.
