OL,3,CWhy I travelled the country asking
OL,4,CMuslims what Ramadan means to them
OL,6,FIt was a deeply spiritual experience
OL,7,Fand while those who are doing it will
OL,8,Fdo it for the last ten nights of
OL,9,FRamadan, my one night was enough for
OL,10,Fme to feel like I was transported away
OL,11,Ffrom our modern-day world.
OL,13,FSimilarly at the East London Mosque,
OL,14,Fwhere I was for the busiest night of
OL,15,Fthe year, the 27th night of Ramadan,
OL,16,Fthought to be the night of power.
